<table id="_ctl2_pnlModuleContent" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
<table id="_ctl2_lstAnnouncements" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="4" Summary="Announcements Design Table" border="0">
		<tr>
			<td>
			
			<span class="ItemTitle">
				60+ Focused Pets &nbsp;-&nbsp;14-Apr-2004
			</span>
			<br>
			<span class="Normal">
            In today's patch, VI stated, "60+ focused mage pets are now summoned with a full set of phantom plate equipped."  Apparently, this change was implemented in a previous patch.  This was apparently part of the previous tuning of pets.  This is a benefit to mage efficiency (especially when a pet dies during combat) but not to pet power.
            &nbsp;
            
        </span>
			<br>
		</td>
		</tr><tr>
			<td>
			
			<span class="ItemTitle">
				Pet Enhancement&nbsp;-&nbsp;25-Mar-2004
			</span>
			<br>
			<span class="Normal">
            Today's patch improved magician pets!  Verant has stated that pet foci items were improved to scale better with the magician's progression.  The more powerful the mage, the more powerful the foci, so to speak.  While it's impossible to say at this point just how positive the change is, it reads as a significant pet balance improvement for magicians moreso than other pet classes.  Since damage was not changed significantly, this patch would seem to have the sole effect of increasing a pet's survivability for each level of foci.  Have a commonet on the change?  Let me know!
            &nbsp;
            
        </span>
			<br>
		</td>
		</tr><tr>
			<td>
			
			<span class="ItemTitle">
				Elemental Draw Fix&nbsp;-&nbsp;23-Mar-2004
			</span>
			<br>
			<span class="Normal">
            This morning's patch eliminated the chance for Elemental Draw to crit.  While Verant didn't state specifically that Elemental Siphon was also fixed, we can only hope the spell wasn't overlooked.  Plus, Verant added a couple of mage-beneficial stealth mods to spells...
            &nbsp;
            <a id="_ctl2_lstAnnouncements__ctl2_moreLink" href="/mageportal/admin/Portal/LinkClick.aspx?tabid=1&amp;table=Announcements&amp;field=ItemID&amp;id=48&amp;link=%2fmageportal%2fDesktopDefault.aspx%3ftabid%3d55">
                read more...</a>
        </span>
			<br>
		</td>
		</tr><tr>
			<td>
			
			<span class="ItemTitle">
				New Mage Spell&nbsp;-&nbsp;16-Mar-2004
			</span>
			<br>
			<span class="Normal">
            Verant added Elemental Draw (level 54) to the game today.  The spell does 800 damage to pet (which can crit) in exchange for a 3 mana/tick buff on the mage.  The recourse buff lasts 6 minutes at level 60.  You can find the spell on Rushka Deklamoor in the EC tunnel.  My price was 157pp.
            &nbsp;
            
        </span>
			<br>
		</td>
		</tr><tr>
			<td>
			
			<span class="ItemTitle">
				New Topic - AAXP Ranking&nbsp;-&nbsp;22-Feb-2004
			</span>
			<br>
			<span class="Normal">
            Added a topic that indicates my opinion of the various AAXP available to the magician class.
            &nbsp;
            <a id="_ctl2_lstAnnouncements__ctl4_moreLink" href="/mageportal/admin/Portal/LinkClick.aspx?tabid=1&amp;table=Announcements&amp;field=ItemID&amp;id=42&amp;link=%2fmageportal%2fDesktopDefault.aspx%3ftabid%3d68">
                read more...</a>
        </span>
			<br>
		</td>
		</tr>
	</table>

</td></tr></table>

